Plan text: The United States should disarm of all of its nuclear forces 

Advantage 1 is A Feminist Paradigm Shift

Nuclear Weapons are the ultimate patriarchal tool which lead to violent oppression and a idealisation of nuclear war. 
Acheson, Director of Reaching Critical Will, 2018 (Ray Acheson, "A feminist critique of the atomic bomb" https://www.boell.de/en/2018/10/12/feminist-critique-atomic-bomb) 

Patriarchal forms of war construction actively promote nuclear use and capabilities, thereby increasing the probability and risk of unending war. The biggest and only nuclear/near-nuclear incidents were due to patriarchy.  [replace card] 
Volo, July 2022, (Lorraine Bayard de Volo, “Masculinity and the Cuban Missile Crisis: gender as pre-emptive deterrent, Professor of gender studies at University of Colorado Boulder, https://www.researchgate.net/publication/361780943_Masculinity_and_the_Cuban_Missile_Crisis_gender_as_pre-emptive_deterrent)

Extinction outweighs, SPECIFICALLY due to its impact on otherised people. Without recognizing this the aff is in infinite failure. 
Nathan Sears 20, PhD Candidate in Political Science at The University of Toronto and Trudeau Fellow in Peace, Conflict and Justice at the Munk School of Global Affairs, 4/17/20, “Existential Security: Towards a Security Framework for the Survival of Humanity,” https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/1758-5899.12800 

Patriarchal nuclear war promotion drives Orientalism and justifies military violence against women of colour. --> make extension? --> Rehighlight???
Nayak ’06 (Meghana; Professor of Political Science at Pace University; March 2006; International Feminist Journal of Politics, 8:1; “Orientalism and ‘saving’ US state identity after 9/11; http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/14616740500415458, accessed 7/14/16) 

The capitalist and colonial concept of “progress” has been established through a gendered division of global labor, which ignores the natural capital of local communities and requires a paradigm of individualism. Plan solves 
Bedford 17—Anna Bedford, “Ecofeminism in Dialogue” chapter 1, ‘Ecofeminist, Post-colonial, and Anti-capitalist Possibilities in Nalo Hopkinson’s Brown Girl in the Ring 2017, Lexington Books, https://ebookcentral-proquest-com.libproxy.newschool.edu/lib/newschool/detail.action?pq-origsite=primo&docID=5188278 

Advantage 2 is Environment:

Nuclear Security narratives feminise the earth itself specifically with respect to extraction—mother earth is there to be plundered, or to be protected by the male weapon. Resistance retools this framing, and so does the plan. 
Traci Brynne Voyles, Professor and Chair of Women’s and Gender Studies at the University of Oklahoma, 2010, “Decolonizing Cartographies: Sovereignty, Territoriality, and Maps of Meaning in the Uranium Landscape”, UC San Diego Electronic Theses and Dissertations, https://escholarship.org/uc/item/6h30w26p, 9-5-23, -PGR 

Environmentalism and Feminism are deeply Linked.
